or, Devon, England":"Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Stawell, Somerset, England":"Stawell, Somerset, England"},"en":{"1345–28 February 1385":"1345–28 February 1385","1330–1372":"1330–1372","1366–Male":"1366–Deceased","1368–1441":"1368–1441","1345–1385":"1345–1385","1368":"1368","1345":"1345","1366":"1366","28 February 1385":"28 February 1385","1441":"1441","1385":"1385","1330":"1330","about 1368":"about 1368","1372":"1372","1382":"1382","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Wormegay, Norfolk, England":"Wormegay, Norfolk, England","Stowell, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Stowell, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Merewode Manor, Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","Stawell, Somerset, England":"Stawell, Somerset, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bardolph","type":"LAST","meanings":["From the name Bertulph; renowned for help."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":37,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Bardolph was born in 1345, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with Richard Hody. She died on 28 February 1385, in Wormegay, Norfolk, England, at the age of 40."},"et":{"1345–28 February 1385":"1345–28. veebruar 1385","1330–1372":"1330–1372","1366–Male":"1366–Surnud","1368–1441":"1368–1441","1345–1385":"1345–1385","1368":"1368","1345":"1345","1366":"1366","28 February 1385":"28. veebruar 1385","1441":"1441","1385":"1385","1330":"1330","about 1368":"umbes 1368","1372":"1372","1382":"1382","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Wormegay, Norfolk, England":"Wormegay, Norfolk, England","Stowell, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Stowell, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Merewode Manor, Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stawell, Somerset, England":"Stawell, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"1345–28 February 1385":"1345–28. helmikuuta 1385","1330–1372":"1330–1372","1366–Male":"1366–Kuollut","1368–1441":"1368–1441","1345–1385":"1345–1385","1368":"1368","1345":"1345","1366":"1366","28 February 1385":"28. helmikuuta 1385","1441":"1441","1385":"1385","1330":"1330","about 1368":"noin 1368","1372":"1372","1382":"1382","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Wormegay, Norfolk, England":"Wormegay, Norfolk, England","Stowell, Somerset, 